<div id="review_3764893355" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3764893355" />
    <a title="Velma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1843025-velma"><img alt="Velma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611872131p2/1843025.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3764893355?book_show_action=true">Jan 19, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Velma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Velma" href="/user/show/1843025-velma">Velma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781111805173" href="/book/show/38220576-helliconia-summer">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=2021-reads">2021-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=library-comma-support-your-local">library-comma-support-your-local</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3764893355" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3178970622564636715">Combining elements of both science fiction and fantasy, Brian Aldiss’ Helliconia trilogy is an epic spanning thousands of years across multiple planets. A masterpiece of world building, its strength lies in the breadth of disciplines from which Aldiss draws. History, anthropology, biology, climate science, astronomy, and political science all undergird three stand-alone stories that are linked by a Gaia-inspired environmental thesis in an attempt to ask questions about religion, spirituality, su</span>
  <span id="freeText3178970622564636715" style="display:none">Combining elements of both science fiction and fantasy, Brian Aldiss’ Helliconia trilogy is an epic spanning thousands of years across multiple planets. A masterpiece of world building, its strength lies in the breadth of disciplines from which Aldiss draws. History, anthropology, biology, climate science, astronomy, and political science all undergird three stand-alone stories that are linked by a Gaia-inspired environmental thesis in an attempt to ask questions about religion, spirituality, survival, community, and government.<br /><br />Helliconia Spring, the first volume, took me a long time to get into, but I’m glad I stuck with it. The ending hooked me. The middle installment, Helliconia Summer, is my favorite; it has the best character development, IMO. Finally, Helliconia Winter was a little ambitious and went a little off the rails in places, but wrapped up the trilogy in a satisfying way. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3178970622564636715" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


